    "title": "Hearty Healthy Green Shakshuka",
    "content": "A dish that has existed in Mediterranean and Arabic cultures for centuries, shakshuka (\"a mixture\" in Tunisian Arabic), is a stew of eggs poached in tomatoes, peppers, onions, garlic and olive oil spiced with a touch of paprika and nutmeg. Here, the famously red stew is transformed into a healthy green one with kale and baby spinach. We're even using green peppers instead of typical red ones for a gorgeous green look. Spoon into it and lick up, you'll be sure to get a complete dose of protein and nutrients at the start of your day.",
