    "content": "Ikan Salai Masak Lemak, or Smoked Tilapia in Coconut Gravy, is one of the dishes that remind me of the days spent with my family in Melaka. Smoking the tilapia with coconut husk helps to remove the muddy flavors commonly found in freshwater fish, but if you can\u2019t obtain coconut husk or shell for smoking, raw rice is a suitable alternative which adds a nice aroma to your smoke. The key to a great Masak Lemak gravy is to use fresh turmeric as it gives the dish the vibrant yellow hue that it is famously known for. This delicious Malaysian kampung dish is certainly one that you must try!",
