    "title": "Lok Lok Sauce",
    "content": "Lok Lok are tiny bite-sized food skewered on a stick and then dipped into hot water to cook. This communal styled steamboat is an Asian favorite and is found in many street stalls around Malaysia and Singapore. But the true magic lies in its dipping sauce which offers spicy, sour, and earthy notes. Lok Lok without Lok Lok Sauce would simply not be as delicious. ",
