    "title": "Cireng Bumbu Rujak",
    "content": "A popular street snack with Sundanese origins, Cireng is usually made with basic ingredients of tapioca starch, water and garlic. Known for its crispy exterior and chewy interior, this addictive treat can be enjoyed in multiple ways - steamed, egg-coated, or even stuffed with meat. While Cireng can be eaten on its own or simply dipped in chili sauce, it is served with a spicy nutty rujak sauce in this quick and easy recipe.",
