    "title": "Kangkung Telur Puyuh (Water Spinach with Quail Eggs)",
    "content": "This Chinese inspired dish is famous in Indonesia and commonly served as a side dish with steamed rice for sahur and also when breaking fast. Whilst the dish traditionally uses water spinach, any green leafy vegetable can be used as a substitute.",
