    "title": "Daging Betutu",
    "content": "Daging Betutu is a tender and aromatic beef dish that can be served with warm rice for the perfect for lunch or dinner. A Balinese specialty that is popular across Indonesia and beyond, it is traditionally prepared by wrapping the spiced meat in palm leaves and roasting with husk charcoal for hours. This recipe offers an easy way to replicate this authentic dish while still retaining the essence and signature rich flavors of the betutu. ",
