    "id": "6c51de0d893b11eda36d8b51443f2256",
    "title": "Sayur Rebung",
    "content": "Bamboo shoots are quite common in Asian cuisine, including Indonesia. Known as rebung, it is often cooked into a side dish like in this hearty Sayur Rebung. Try this timeless recipe to enjoy it with your family and friends. All you need to do is stew these bamboo shoots in coconut milk and aromatic spices, and you\u2019re guaranteed to get everyone excited for lunch. Delectably spicy with flavors that tingle, you can pair these tender bamboo shoot pieces with a plate of warm rice.",
