    "id": "6d809c52893b11eda36d8b51443f2256",
    "title": "Oseng Ati Ampela Kentang",
    "content": "From intestine skewers to fried chicken feet, Indonesians love to chomp down all parts of a chicken. Gizzards and chicken livers are especially favored by many! Rich in proteins and easier on the wallet, they\u2019re a great alternative to chicken meat and can be made into Oseng Ati Ampela Kentang. Stir fried potatoes, gizzard and liver are seasoned with spices like shallots, garlic and chili to make a spicy and savory side dish that is a must-have on your dining table for iftar during the fasting month of Ramadan. Prepare a big batch for dinner so you can enjoy it again for sahur (pre-dawn meal).",
    "image_url": "https://asianfoodnetwork.com/content/dam/afn/global/en/recipes/oseng-ati-ampela-kentang/OsengAtiAmpelaKentang_Article_1920x1280_4.jpg.transform/recipestep-img/img.jpg",
    "ingredients": [
        "300 g Potatoes",
        "200 g Chicken Liver",
        "200 g Chicken Gizzards",
        "70 g Shallots",
        "50 g Garlic",
        "70 g Big Red Chili",
        "70 g Big Green Chili",
        "50 g Onions",
        "2 Red Tomatoes",
        "3 g Salt",
        "10 g Sugar",
        "13 g Chicken Powder",
        "30 g Sweet Soy Sauce",
        "650 ml Cooking oil",
        "50 ml Water"
    ],
    "instructions": [
        {
            "title": "Prepare the chicken liver, gizzard and potatoes",
            "contents": [
                "Dice the chicken liver, chicken gizzards and potatoes into 1cm cubes.",
                "Preheat a pan with half of the oil for 5 mins on medium heat.",
                "Add the diced liver, gizzards and potatoes, fry until cooked or about 10 mins.",
                "Remove from heat and set aside."
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Prepare the spice paste",
            "contents": [
                "Into a blender or food processor, add shallots, garlic, large red chilies, large green chilies, onions, red tomatoes and 100 ml of water. Blend until smooth."
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Saut\u00e9 ingredients",
            "contents": [
                "Preheat a pan with 50ml cooking oil on medium heat.",
                "Once the oil is hot, pour the blended spice paste into the pan and saut\u00e9 for about 10 minutes.\u00a0",
                "Reduce heat, and add the fried liver, gizzards and potatoes.\u00a0",
                "Add sugar, salt, chicken powder, and sweet soy sauce. Stir to combine."
            ]
        }
    ],
