    "title": "Kikil Rice Bowl (Beef Tendon Rice Bowl)",
    "content": "Kikil Rice Bowl is an exquisite Indonesian rice dish with kikil (gravel beef) as a topping. Rice bowl is a Japanese cuisine, called donburi, usually consists of warm white rice with various kinds of side dishes on it, such as fish, meat and vegetables. Indonesians have adopted and adapted rice bowl recipes with stronger and bolder flavors to suit the local palate and frequently have this meal for office lunches. It is even available on restaurant menus.",
