    "title": "Wajik (Sticky Rice Cake with Palm Sugar)",
    "content": "This sweet sticky rice cake is commonly found in Indonesia, Malaysia and Brunei. In Bahasa Indonesia,  the term wajik is used to describe the shape of a diamond, but that isn\u2019t the only gem about Wajik. This traditional snack made of steamed glutinous rice cooked in palm sugar, coconut milk, and pandan leaves is a delectable treat for all. ",
